Responsibilities

Working closely with PM, Designers, Developers and Programmers
Understand the client's requirements and generate technical solutions
Identify issues and implement solutions to complex problems
Perform function enhancement, system deployment and testing

Requirements


Higher Diploma / Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or any related disciplines;
1 year or above experience in web or application development;
Experience in PHP framework (e.g. Laravel, Codeigniter), MySql, MSSQL, RESTful API, HTML, CSS, JavaScript framework (e.g. React, bootstrap), Python will be an advantage;
Experience in payment integration (e.g. Paypal / Stripe) will be an advantage;
Good team player with strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
Self-motivated with can do attitude and timely delivery results
Working Location in Tsuen Wan

Nice to have

Experience in cloud storage, deployment and computing. We use Azure / AWS but we're open to other platform experience

Job Description: 
Systems development, enhancement and maintenance;
Perform unit tests;
Prepare program specification;
Perform any other duties assigned. 
Job Requirements: 

Degree holder in Computer Science or related disciplines;
At least 2 years related working experience for analyst programmer;
Knowledge in Java, SQL is required;
Knowledge in any of Spring, Javascript/Typescript, React, React Native, MQ is a plus;
Good analytical skill, commitment to work, good problem-solving skill;
Candidate with less experience or fresh graduate will also be considered as Programmer.

Responsibilities:

- Analyze, design, develop, implement for real-time, low-latency mobile applications;
- Conduct program testing, system testing and develop test cases to support user acceptance test;
- Assist team leader in requirement study, documentation and co-ordination;
- Provide ongoing user and application support;

Requirements:

- University Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Electronic Engineering or equivalent;
- 2+ yrs experiences in Flutter/React Native application development;
- Solid knowledge in React Native libraries, frameworks
- Experience in Objective-C/Swift (for iOS) or Java/Kotlin (for Android) or JavaScript, ReactJS is a plus;
- Extremely enthusiastic in programming and learning new technologies
- Willing to learn, responsible, a good team player with good communication skills;
- Self-motivated, work independently, good analytical and problem solving skill;
- Experience in Agile/Scrum development is a plus.

Job Description:

Analyze existing IT system and develop IT solution for new enhancements;
Provide daily support to operational and ad-hoc issues;
Assist teams with smaller related projects related to primary application system.
Requirement:

Degree holder in Information Technology or other related disciplines;
2 years of Java (Spring) and Javascript Development experience;
Good knowledge of SQL and writing Stored Procedures (Preferably SQL Server);
Self-motivated, strong sense of responsibility, good analytical, problem solving skills and attention to details.

Interested parties please send full resume with employment history and expected salary to HRA Division, Yusen Logistics Global Management Limited at Level 31, Tower 1, Kowloon Commerce Centre, 51 Kwai Cheong Road, Kwai Chung, N.T. or by email to hr.ylhk @ hk.yusen-logistics.com     

Yusen Logistics Global Management Limited is an equal opportunity employer. All information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Your Role

To develop applications on mobile platforms (Flutter / iOS / Android / React Native)
To be responsible for design, development, testing, implementation, enhancement and maintenance
To implement systems to meet dynamic business needs riding on the latest and proven technology;
To assist in the company’s digital transformation initiatives and build related common and re-usable components;
To cultivate and train development team members to fast-track with mobile app development technique;
To appreciate latest technological development and adapt for application development productivity

To succeed in this role

Degree / Higher Diploma in Computer Science, Information Engineering or equivalent;
Minimum of 2-3 years’ software development experience, in which at least 1 year on mobile application development;
Hands-on experience on HTML, XML, Json, JSP, Shell scripts, Git;
Working knowledge of Objective-C/Swift and JAVA/Kotlin-Android;
Knowledge of Java / Spring, Flutter/React, Cloud (AWS) technology is an advantages;
Possess solid organizational and technical skills to effectively manage multiple priorities;
Self-motivated, good customer-oriented attitude and ability to work under pressure;
Eager to learn new technology;
Sound knowledge of Development / Ops practice;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese

Roles and responsibilities:

-          Developing innovative Websites, Digital Applications based on the supplied design;
-          Exploring on new technology to meet different project requirements;
-          Work closely with all colleagues in creative, development team and clients to ensure requirements and schedule are met.

 Requirements:

3 years+ working experience in related industry;
Solid knowledge and experience in PHP / MySQL / Javascript ;
Familiar with different web CMS system would be a Big Advantage;
Basic knowledge in HTML / CSS is needed;
Experience with any Frameworks is an added bonus;
Proven experience and understanding of responsive design;
Efficient, self-motivated and able to work independently to meet multiple project deadlines;

Benefits:
-          5 days work
-          Competitive salary
-          Medical Insurance
-          Performance Bonus
-          Free Snacks
-          Casual attire

For interested parties, please email full resume with proven portfolio and expected salary to us through "Apply Now" button.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities:

Prepare proposal and tender documents in response to clients’ requirements;
Development of data conversion and migration plan and strategies;
Conducting requirement and justification studies;
Analysis, design and implementation of multi-tier web application systems;
Ensuring conformance of software packages against user requirement ; and
Lead a team of programmer for application development and project implementation.

Requirements: 

Degree holder in computer science, computer engineering, information technology and or related disciplines;
With at least of 5 years’ experience in system analysis and design, reporting solutions and or other web application development projects;
Must have specialty experience relating to the implementation of data warehouse, business intelligence and data analysis system;
Must be proficient in Windows and Unix Platform;
Solid experience in .Net, C#, JAVA and JavaScript is highly preferred;
Good writing skills for documentation;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills; and
Good command of both spoken and written English.


Please send your full detailed resume with expected salary and date available to The Human Resources Manager, NEC Hong Kong Limited, 25th Floor, The Metropolis Tower, 10 Metropolis Drive, Hunghom, Kowloon or by e-mail.

Personal data provided by job applicant will be used strictly in accordance with employer's personal data policy, a copy of which will be provided immediately upon request.

Duties: The appointees will be responsible for the development and support of core IT application systems.

Requirements:

A Bachelor’s Degree / Associate Degree / Higher Diploma in Information Technology, Computer Science or related disciplines;
At least two years’ working experience in application system development or support services;
Hands-on experience with web application development and PL/SQL programming;
Knowledge in web-based system design and application security definitely an advantage;
Good oral and written communication skills in both Chinese and English; and
High-calibre fresh graduates are also welcome.

Employment Terms:  The remuneration package will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Appointment will be on a fixed-term contract with contract-end-gratuity, MPF benefits, medical and dental care.  Future employment may be offered on renewable contracts subject to performance and staffing needs.

Date for Application Review: 7 February 2022

Applications would be considered until the post is filled.

